      "description": "This 1994 Mazda RX-7 (FD3S) is a museum-grade specimen featuring the iconic 13B-REW rotary powerplant. The sequential twin-turbocharger system has been rigorously inspected, ensuring a seamless transition and peak boost pressure across the RPM range without vacuum line degradation. Mechanically, the vehicle is superlative; compression tests yield high, even results across all rotor faces. The chassis retains its factory-spec double-wishbone suspension and Torsen limited-slip differential, delivering the precise, neutral handling characteristics the FD is renowned for. The 5-speed manual transmission shifts with clinical accuracy, paired with a firm, responsive clutch. This is a zero-fault, numbers-matching example with original paint and an immaculate interior, preserved for the serious collector who demands mechanical purity.",
